Brothers.

15:56.078 --> 15:58.517
Brethren. Sistren.

15:58.550 --> 16:00.486
Yes.

16:00.520 --> 16:03.459
Here we are.

16:03.492 --> 16:07.133
Thoust can take the mattresses.
I prefer the hard ground.

16:07.166 --> 16:10.073
Uh, I do have a couple
of foldy chairs. You can

16:10.106 --> 16:12.511
figure out your
sleep situations. Um...

16:12.544 --> 16:16.218
I do have one toothbrush. Uh...

16:16.251 --> 16:18.456
It's kind of multipurpose,
but you're all welcome to it.

16:18.489 --> 16:19.792
Please, for the love
of all things holy,

16:19.825 --> 16:21.529
keep your hands off of my

16:21.562 --> 16:24.602
metal detector,
and, yes, come in.

16:24.635 --> 16:26.573
Come in to thine stable.

16:26.606 --> 16:29.077
Ah. Mm.

16:31.248 --> 16:33.219
Ah... All right.

16:33.252 --> 16:35.290
Hey.

16:35.323 --> 16:38.062
We can't just stop.
We kind of got to go

16:38.095 --> 16:39.330
to the beach.

16:42.638 --> 16:46.445
- We can't stay here.
- Fuck no, bro.
- I know, bro.

16:46.478 --> 16:49.084
Ah, you're far better off
here than you are

16:49.117 --> 16:51.254
out there on your own at night.

16:53.693 --> 16:56.600
Listen, the beach is five miles

16:56.633 --> 16:59.237
straight down this road.

16:59.270 --> 17:02.076
In the morning,
I'll take you there myself.

17:04.782 --> 17:06.553
Okay?

17:06.586 --> 17:07.754
Please.

17:10.359 --> 17:12.565
All right, yeah.
Fuck it, we'll stay.

17:12.598 --> 17:14.736
Just for the night, okay?

17:14.769 --> 17:17.742
We'll stand guard, all right?

17:17.775 --> 17:20.413
We'll take shifts.
Yeah?

17:20.446 --> 17:23.385
- Yeah.
- Okay.

17:30.634 --> 17:34.241
I mean, everyone
knows him for <i>Lost Boys,</i>

17:34.274 --> 17:37.280
but he did <i>Thunderdome,</i> too,
and he toured

17:37.313 --> 17:39.418
with Tina Turner for years.

17:39.451 --> 17:41.221
Is that the guy in the diaper?

17:41.254 --> 17:44.161
No, that's, um, Ton Ton Tattoo.

17:44.194 --> 17:47.267
Oh. Wait, so there's
two sax players

17:47.300 --> 17:49.539
- in <i>Thunderdome?</i>
- No, Tim Cappello

17:49.572 --> 17:51.543
wasn't in the movie.

17:51.576 --> 17:53.747
He-he just did the song
in the credits.

17:53.780 --> 17:57.219
Oh. Got it.

17:59.391 --> 18:01.563
Daniel showed me that movie.

18:01.596 --> 18:04.702
- Which one?
- Both, actually.

18:06.471 --> 18:08.108
Same.

18:08.943 --> 18:10.748
He was my hero, you know?

18:10.781 --> 18:13.219
Tim Cappello?

18:13.252 --> 18:15.390
No. Uh, Daniel.

18:15.423 --> 18:18.195
Um, it just seemed like
he could do anything, you know?

18:22.504 --> 18:25.176
Me too.

18:25.209 --> 18:27.113
I think the same about you,
you know?

18:28.550 --> 18:29.519
: Really?

18:29.552 --> 18:31.422
Yeah. I mean,

18:31.455 --> 18:33.192
it just seems like,
anytime we get into trouble,

18:33.225 --> 18:35.363
you just know what to do.

18:37.534 --> 18:39.539
That's fucking stupid, Cheese.

18:41.441 --> 18:44.716
I have no idea
what to do right now.

18:46.986 --> 18:49.324
If anyone can make it out,

18:49.357 --> 18:50.727
it'd be you.

18:54.668 --> 18:57.207
- LAPD! Let's go!

19:00.279 --> 19:02.217
Shit. Better get the fuck up.
Get the fuck up.

19:02.250 --> 19:04.321
- Fuck up.
- What the fuck's
going on?

19:04.354 --> 19:06.225
Mm, I was dreaming, bro.

19:06.258 --> 19:07.895
- Cops are here, bro.
- What?

19:07.928 --> 19:10.601
- Come on, we got to go.
- What... what time is it?

19:10.634 --> 19:12.437
- Oh, shit.

19:12.470 --> 19:15.343
- Move! Let's go! Go!

19:15.376 --> 19:16.646
Where's White Jesus?

19:16.679 --> 19:18.215
Fucking dipped out on us
hella long ago, bro.

19:18.248 --> 19:20.419
Uh, he'll forever
live on in our hearts.

19:30.874 --> 19:31.943
<i>
Guys,</i>

19:31.976 --> 19:33.780
I can't go any further.

19:33.813 --> 19:35.717
You guys go on without me.

19:35.750 --> 19:38.623
Fuck, Cheese, man. Come on, bro,
we're almost there.

19:38.656 --> 19:41.529
- You said that, like,
four hours ago, bro.

19:41.562 --> 19:43.966
Just admit it, you don't know
where we're going.

19:44.969 --> 19:47.006
We're just following
the directions

19:47.039 --> 19:49.945
- of White Jesus, Willie Jack.
- Yeah.

19:53.285 --> 19:54.622
The fuck?

19:54.655 --> 19:56.559
That motherfucker
was walking fast as shit.

19:56.592 --> 19:58.028
Can't stay here.

19:58.061 --> 19:59.532
Don't want to get picked up
by some white lady

19:59.565 --> 20:01.435
who likes ranch dressing
on her dinner rolls.

20:01.468 --> 20:03.907
Yeah. Exactly.

20:03.940 --> 20:07.648
Elora, you have some
really, really specific fears.

20:07.681 --> 20:08.950
Wait.

20:08.983 --> 20:10.687
What?

20:10.720 --> 20:13.794
- You guys hear that?

20:13.827 --> 20:14.928
Yo.

20:28.890 --> 20:32.297
It just... keeps going.

20:32.330 --> 20:34.969
It's like
a big-ass lake that never ends.

20:35.002 --> 20:36.639
Unreal.

20:46.792 --> 20:49.497
(sighs) Skoden.

22:51.474 --> 22:52.878
- Skoden.
- Ooh.

23:02.764 --> 23:04.067
Come on, bro.

23:04.100 --> 23:06.071
You got to put your feet
in the sand. Feel it.

23:06.104 --> 23:08.643
Nope.

23:08.676 --> 23:11.582
I know what we came here
to do, but...

23:13.051 --> 23:15.455
I don't want
to let him go, Bear.

23:19.197 --> 23:22.738
Hey.
Hey, Elora, we're not.

23:22.771 --> 23:25.142
It's...

23:25.175 --> 23:27.013
it's the pain.

23:27.046 --> 23:29.150
That's what we're letting go.

23:29.183 --> 23:31.020
It's got us stuck.

23:32.924 --> 23:34.628
Just imagine

23:34.661 --> 23:37.968
how happy Danny would be
seeing us live our lives.

23:38.001 --> 23:40.472
Finally in Cali.

23:56.839 --> 24:00.179
- Ready?
- Uh, yeah.

24:00.212 --> 24:02.016
Okay.

24:23.058 --> 24:25.730
What now? Without the letter?

24:27.667 --> 24:30.072
<i>She's a good girl ♪</i>

24:30.105 --> 24:33.680
<i>Loves some aunties ♪</i>

24:33.713 --> 24:37.621
<i>Loves White Jesus ♪</i>

24:37.654 --> 24:39.558
<i>And America, too... ♪</i>

24:39.591 --> 24:41.829
Hey, trust us, this works.

24:41.862 --> 24:45.904
<i>Loves her horses and... ♪</i>

24:45.937 --> 24:48.977
Fuck, I can't remember the rest.

24:49.010 --> 24:50.614
It's all good, bro.

24:50.647 --> 24:52.283
Hey, Cheese.

24:52.316 --> 24:55.122
Why don't you say a prayer?

24:55.155 --> 24:56.893
You're good at it.

24:56.926 --> 24:59.297
Little long, but...
go for it, bro.

24:59.330 --> 25:02.838
- You got this.
- Uh...

25:02.871 --> 25:03.973
Okay.

25:04.006 --> 25:06.010
Um, well...

25:07.948 --> 25:11.321
He/She...

25:11.354 --> 25:14.895
Hers/His/They...

25:14.928 --> 25:16.866
genderless being,

25:16.899 --> 25:20.139
we're here for
our friend Daniel.

25:20.172 --> 25:21.742
Um...

25:21.775 --> 25:24.313
well, we just wanted this moment
to be significant.

25:26.317 --> 25:28.756
Like in the movies.

25:28.789 --> 25:30.627
Like in <i>NeverEnding Story</i> when

25:30.660 --> 25:32.764
the wind blows down
to the basement, and

25:32.797 --> 25:33.900
Bastian realized
that he's been reading

25:33.933 --> 25:35.302
about himself, but, like,

25:35.335 --> 25:37.073
his inner-self
was actually Atreyu,

25:37.106 --> 25:38.075
- and...
- Cheese.

25:38.108 --> 25:39.945
Sorry.

25:39.978 --> 25:42.049
Keep going, bro.

25:44.053 --> 25:46.124
We didn't get to say goodbye
to you, Daniel.

25:47.828 --> 25:49.932
And, um...

25:49.965 --> 25:53.673
you know what?
To be honest, I've been...

25:53.706 --> 25:55.075
kind of mad at you.

25:57.948 --> 26:00.051
You're my hero, man.

26:02.223 --> 26:05.228
Now you're not here
to make things right or better.

26:07.266 --> 26:09.237
And Willie Jack,

26:09.270 --> 26:12.243
she cares for
her family members.

26:12.276 --> 26:14.648
And now she's lost a brother,

26:14.681 --> 26:16.819
cousin, friend.

26:18.956 --> 26:21.696
And Bear...

26:21.729 --> 26:24.067
he lost his best friend.

26:24.100 --> 26:27.808
Now, a whole piece
of him's missing.

26:27.841 --> 26:29.143
And Elora...

26:29.176 --> 26:32.216
she lost her hope.

26:32.249 --> 26:34.688
Whenever she looked
into the future,

26:34.721 --> 26:36.357
she'd see you there, man.

26:38.128 --> 26:40.266
You're our brother.

26:40.299 --> 26:43.973
Remember you for all the
good things we've done together.

26:45.375 --> 26:47.346
And we're out here for you, man.

26:49.183 --> 26:50.820
We just hope we're doing
the right thing.

26:54.895 --> 26:56.798
Cheese.

27:06.050 --> 27:07.788
I love you, bitches.

27:09.423 --> 27:12.362
Fucking love you guys.

27:19.745 --> 27:21.716
Let's go all the way in.

27:21.749 --> 27:23.251
Yeah?

27:31.434 --> 27:32.871
Coming?

27:33.906 --> 27:35.409
I'm scared of what's in there.

27:35.442 --> 27:38.750
Fuck, man, me too, bro.

27:38.783 --> 27:40.987
I won't let you drown.

27:55.917 --> 27:57.153
Fucking hell!

27:57.186 --> 27:59.023
- Shit!

27:59.056 --> 28:00.125
It's freezing!

28:07.072 --> 28:08.943
We did it.

28:12.951 --> 28:16.792
<i>In the stinta ♪</i>

28:16.825 --> 28:19.497
<i>Gray and white salmon ♪</i>

28:19.531 --> 28:21.234
<i>Swim upstream... ♪</i>

28:21.267 --> 28:22.938
Told you you'd
make it here, Daniel.

28:25.510 --> 28:27.246
<i>Yellow underneath... ♪</i>

28:47.386 --> 28:49.525
- Love you, bitch.
- Love you, bitch!

29:08.863 --> 29:10.065
So, what do we do now?

29:11.568 --> 29:14.173
Gonna find out
where the fuck my car is.

29:14.206 --> 29:17.279
I owe Kenny Boy,
got to bring it back.

29:17.312 --> 29:21.254
My uncle Cvto lives
on a rez nearby.

29:21.287 --> 29:23.358
Maybe he can help us.

29:26.030 --> 29:27.567
I'm not going back.

29:40.092 --> 29:42.129
- Follow me.

30:07.914 --> 30:10.486
Blessed are those
who have not seen

30:10.520 --> 30:12.557
and yet still believe.

30:13.526 --> 30:15.563
I still believe.

30:51.501 --> 30:55.108
